{"_id":"96rJI71zlf93bFqB","name":"Rules","content":"<p><strong>Rule 1:</strong></p>\n<p>When you die, your soul becomes exposed. If it is not interfered with, you will revive in Homestead 24 hours later with only the items forged from your own soul. If your soul is tampered with, then the item created from it will contain your essense and must be unmade for you to return to life.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 2:</strong></p>\n<p>If you read the description of a lootable item then you are holding it and examining it. </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 3:</strong></p>\n<p>If you lose XP your level remains the same however you will lose level benefits beginning when you cross the level threshold below your current level.<br /><br />Level 11: 85000 XP<br />Level 10: 64000 XP<br />Level 9: 48000 XP<br />Level 8: 34000 XP<br /><br />If you are at level 10 and lose XP you will retain all level 10 features until you are below 48000 XP at which point you will still be level 10 but will only have level 9 features. The same thing will happen if you go below 34000 XP. If you begin gaining XP again, you will regain lost features in the same way. Until you return to your current level at which point leveling works as normal.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Rule 4:</strong><br />Soul forging allows the creation of items from the living world in the land of the dead. <br /><br /><strong>Rule 5:</strong><br />Lesser and Greater souls<br /><br />- lesser souls are worth a fixed amount (1000 xp) and can be used to craft non-magical items.<br />- There should be around 1000 of these lesser souls available in the game.<br />- The conversion between gold and lesser souls is: Round Up((gold*10)/1000)</p>\n<p>Greater souls are worth a variable amount and can be used to craft specific magic items. <br /><br /><strong>Rule 6:</strong><br />Life Amulet: Each turn you are below max HP, gain 2d10 hit points</p>\n<p>Death <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: If an effect would reduce you to 0 hit points, instead you remain at 1 HP and take 1 point of exhaustion</span></p>\n<p>Energy <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: If you have 0 spell slots, gain 1 random spell slot you have access to.</span></p>\n<p>Will <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You cannot fail wisdom or intelligence saving throws</span></p>\n<p>Earth <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You cannot fail Strength or Constitution saving throws</span></p>\n<p>Balance <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: Whenever you gain hit points, that many hit points are lost divided among the creatures within 30 feet of you. Whenever you lose hit points, that many hit points are gained divided among the creatures within 30 feet of you</span></p>\n<p>Time <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Amulet</span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: You always go first in any combat, and have 1 legendary resistance per day </span></p>","folder":"l2BnOQQTdztiQFWG","sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"vmPmArlBOnlDRCNW":3},"flags":{}}
